  "name": "Sanctuary",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>This spell prevents creatures from attacking the caster or the spell's recipient. Any creature attempting to attack a warded character must make a charisma saving throw in order to make the attack. A failed save means that the attacker ignores the person under the spell (it does not lose its attack, but must choose another target). If the warded character attacks or casts offensive spells then the <em>sanctuary</em> spell is negated. This spell does not prevent the warded creature from being affected by area of effect spells.</p>",
